yle image and the shopping list/loading phase diagram: Using Tool | Doc Insert Insert content at line 843 Excellent! Now let me add the fiber loading phase diagram and the shopping list visual: Using Tool | Doc Insert Insert content at line 876 Perfect! Let me add the shopping list visual image to the meal prep chapter. Let me find that section: Using Tool | Doc View Viewing document: 630,655 Using Tool | Doc Insert Insert content at line 639 Perfect! The ebook is looking fantastic with all the key images embedded. Now let me save the document and create a summary. Let me save it to make it accessible: Using Tool | Save document as url Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive knowledge base document to organize all the content we've created: Using Tool | Markdown Generation Generate content before line 1, instruction: Create a comprehensive knowledge base document that organizes all the outputs from this ebook creation project. # NATURAL GLP-1 RESET PROJECT - KNOWLEDGE BASE ## Project Overview **Client Profile:** 49-year-old woman, 5'2\", 180 lbs **Goal:** Lose 5 lbs of fat per month through natural GLP-1 optimization **Source:** Dr. Amin Hedayat's YouTube video on natural GLP-1 boosting **Delivery Format:** 30-page professional ebook with hyperrealistic images --- ## Main Deliverable ### Complete Ebook **Title:** The Natural GLP-1 Reset: Your 14-Day Journey to Metabolic Freedom **Format:** HTML (Professional, print-ready design) **Access URL:** https://www.genspark.ai/api/files/s/VueGk9v7 **Pages:** 30+ pages with comprehensive content **Reading Level:** 9th grade (accessible, clear language) --- ## Content Structure ### **INTRODUCTION** - Understanding your body's natural weight loss system - What is GLP-1 and why it matters - Your specific goal: 5 lbs/month fat loss - How the Mediterranean-inspired protocol works ### **CHAPTER 1: The Science Made Simple - Your Satiety Factory** **Key Concepts:** - The 30-foot digestive tract anatomy - L-cells: Your satiety factory at the end of the intestine - Why modern processed food bypasses L-cells - The Incretin Effect explained simply **Visual Assets:** - Digestive system diagram showing L-cells location - 30-foot intestinal tract illustration ### **CHAPTER 2: The Three Master Keys to Turn Off Hunger** **The 3 Keys:** 1. **Butyrate** - The chemical key (produced by gut bacteria) 2. **Fiber** - The raw material (fermentable fiber feeds bacteria) 3. **Movement** - The mechanical key (IL-6 muscle signals) **Visual Assets:** - Three keys infographic showing Butyrate, Fiber, and Movement ### **CHAPTER 3: The Cold Potato Secret - Resistant Starch Explained** **Key Science:** - Retrogradation: The 24-hour cooling process - RS3 resistant starch crystals - Why cooled potatoes become metabolic gold - The 130°F reheating rule **Best Foods for Resistant Starch:** - Potatoes (all types) - Parboiled rice - Legumes (lentils, beans) - Pasta **Visual Assets:** - Before/after potato transformation diagram - Hot vs. cold molecular structure comparison ### **CHAPTER 4: Your 5-Step Daily Protocol for Metabolic Autonomy** **STEP 1: The Circadian Anchor** - 10-30 minutes morning sunlight before 10am - Alternative: 10,000 lux light box **STEP 2: The Slow Carb Sequence** - Fiber/vegetables first - Wait 5-10 minutes - Protein second - Starches last - Result: 29% increase in GLP-1 **STEP 3: The Resistant Starch Anchor** - 1/2 cup cooled starch with lunch - Targets afternoon cravings **STEP 4: The Kinetic Turbocharger** - 10-minute walk after EVERY meal - Muscles act as \"glucose sponges\" - Mechanically stimulates gut hormones **STEP 5: Circadian Kitchen Closure** - Stop eating 3 hours before bed - Allows \"Migrating Motor Complex\" to clean gut **Visual Assets:** - Circular 5-step protocol infographic - Clock-style daily protocol diagram ### **CHAPTER 5: Food Order Effect - The Pyloric Valve Trick** **The Mechanism:** - Fiber/protein first triggers CCK hormone - CCK tightens pyloric valve - Creates \"slow drip\" instead of flood - Results: Hours longer satiety **Plate Construction:** 1. First: Fiber buffer (salad, veget"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=ebc026f9-fb38-4710-8884-6df75fc98385","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=ebc026f9-fb38-4710-8884-6df75fc98385"}]}]}]
